  <p>
   ODD-(opposite of even)
   <br/>
   When referring to "odd and even" numbers just spell the 
  concepts: O-D-D / E-V-E-N.
  </p>
  <p>
   Some people do the sign "
   <a href="../e/equal.htm">
    EQUAL
   </a>
   " to 
			mean "even."
   <br/>
  </p>
  <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1"/>
 </font>
 <p>
  <font face="Arial">
   <br/>
   The term "odd" can be expressed by using the sign for "STRANGE" but 
if you are 
      talking about "odd numbers" I recommend just
   <i>
    spelling
   </i>
   O-D-D.
  </font>
 </p>
 <p>
 </p>
